Therefore, the conditions for interference are:

    d\sin\theta = 
        \begin{cases} 
        n\lambda \amp n = 0, \pm 1, \pm 2, \cdots \text{Constructive} \\
        \left( n + \frac{1}{2}\right)\lambda \amp n = 0, \pm 1, \pm 2, \cdots \text{Destructive}
        \end{cases} 

Using \left| L_1-L_2 \right| = d\sin\theta, we can express intensity from Eq.  in tems of direction from the slits and slit width as follows. I also rreplace k by 2\pi/\lambda for ease of use.

    I = 2I_0\left[ 1+  \cos \left( \frac{2\pi d}{\lambda} \sin\theta \right)  \right].
